description.narrative: UNICEF's assistance to government focuses on improving the quality of services of primary health care at community level in 6 regions for prenatal consultation, delivery, maternal and newborn essential care, emergency obstetric and neonatal care, post-natal consultation, IMCI and iCCM to prevent and treat diarrhoea, malaria and pneumonia. More than 90% of children were treated appropriately for the three illness and 40% of women delivered in health facilities. UNICEF also supported adolescent health in youth friendly health centres in targeted regions. UNICEF supported Government to develop HSS and MNCAH strategic documents for more engagement in nutrition from 2019 to 2023. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
